---
title: Roasted Red Peppers Stuffed with Ras El Hanout-Spiced Pork
description: Ras el hanout means "head of the shop" in Arabic, which suggests using the best ingredients you can find. We're inclined to agree that this North African spice blend is pretty top-notch. Loaded with warm, fragrant spices like cumin, ginger, and coriander, it has a way of transforming anything it touches. Here, it's used to season pork, which is then stuffed into tender roasted bell peppers and served on a bed of quinoa.
